<vector xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:width="24dp"
    android:height="24dp"
    android:viewportWidth="24"
    android:viewportHeight="24"
    android:tint="?attr/colorControlNormal">
  <!--
    YueLink mark — interlocked rings + cherry-stem V on top.
    Geometry matches assets/icon.png (launcher foreground): rings centered
    at x=9 and x=15 (separation 6) with radius 4.2 produce ~28% overlap,
    same proportion as the brand. The V apex sits at the ring intersection
    so the stems read as part of the ring crown rather than a separate
    fork.

    Earlier draft placed the centers at (8.5, 13.5)/(15.5, 13.5) with a
    filled diamond between them, which read as handcuff cuffs + a key
    shaft (user feedback 2026-04-29). Removing the diamond and pulling
    the rings inward fixes that: stroke-only, rounded caps, no fill.
    System tints the white via colorControlNormal so the tile inherits
    the QS palette automatically.
  -->

  <!-- Left ring -->
  <path
      android:pathData="M9,13 m-4.2,0 a4.2,4.2 0,1,1 8.4,0 a4.2,4.2 0,1,1 -8.4,0"
      android:strokeColor="#FFFFFF"
      android:strokeWidth="2"
      android:strokeLineCap="round"
      android:fillColor="#00000000"/>

  <!-- Right ring -->
  <path
      android:pathData="M15,13 m-4.2,0 a4.2,4.2 0,1,1 8.4,0 a4.2,4.2 0,1,1 -8.4,0"
      android:strokeColor="#FFFFFF"
      android:strokeWidth="2"
      android:strokeLineCap="round"
      android:fillColor="#00000000"/>

  <!-- Cherry-stem V — apex at top of ring intersection, tips diverge upward -->
  <path
      android:pathData="M10.4,4.2 L12,8.8 L13.6,4.2"
      android:strokeColor="#FFFFFF"
      android:strokeWidth="1.6"
      android:strokeLineCap="round"
      android:strokeLineJoin="round"
      android:fillColor="#00000000"/>
</vector>
